The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for program analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on utilizing the known structure of input data, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the modularization of neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR).
